      "message": "1. MD-SAL notification thread (write, on config change) — onEndpointsChanged reassigns it wholesale.                                                                                                                                     \n2. Incoming-connection threads (read, per dial-in) — createContext reads it; several devices can connect concurrently.                                                                                            \n  The race is #2 reading while #1 writes (a device connecting while the endpoint config changes). volatile guarantees the reader sees either the old or the new fully-built immutable object but never a stale or half-published one. No thread does a read-modify-write, so volatile is enough",
